abstract: Hewlett-Packard reports net earnings of $1.32 billion in quarter ended October 30 and revenue of $25.7 billion, down 9 percent from quarter year earlier; quarter is final one for HP as it was once known, as it has been split into separate entities HP Inc and HPE, which were legally one company until end of October.
lead_paragraph: Meg Whitman, who runs the new Hewlett Packard Enterprise, said that the split-off company was off to a strong start.

headline.main: Final Earnings at the Old Hewlett-Packard Fall Short of Wall St. Expectations
headline.print_headline: Last Report From Old HP Still Misses Wall St. Forecasts
